"title": "5195: veil",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5195: veil",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Generally, an item of female dress worn by an unmarried woman in the presence of her future husband and also by a prostitute. Head-coverings were worn by men and women as a sign of mourning. The term is also used metaphorically to indicate a lack of understanding of God's truth. Scripture uses the imagery of “removing a veil” to refer to God's final self-revelation at the end of the age, or the making known of God's will and nature through Jesus Christ or other means.</p>\n<h2>The veil as an item of female dress</h2>\n<h3>Worn by women in general</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:1\">SNG 4:1</a></strong> <em>The veil covered the lower part of the face, so focusing attention on the eyes and temples.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:65\">GEN 24:65</a> <em>Rebekah veils herself in the presence of her future husband, Isaac</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3\">SNG 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song6:7\">SNG 6:7</a></p>\n<h3>Worn by prostitutes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:14-Gen38:15\">GEN 38:14–38:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:7\">SNG 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Worn by female sorcerers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:18\">EZK 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:21\">EZK 13:21</a></p>\n<h3>Worn as a sign of wealth and status</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:19\">ISA 3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:2\">ISA 47:2</a> <em>Babylon's veil will be removed as a mark of her humiliation.</em></p>\n<h2>Veils worn as a sign of grief</h2>\n<h3>Faces covered in sorrow and dismay</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:30\">2SA 15:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:45\">LEV 13:45</a> <em>A veil worn by the ceremonially unclean signifies grief at separation from God</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:4\">JER 14:4</a></p>\n<h3>Veils customarily worn by mourners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:4\">2SA 19:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:17\">EZK 24:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:22\">EZK 24:22</a></p>\n<h3>Faces covered as a sign of disgrace</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:12\">EST 6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth7:8\">EST 7:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic3:7\">MIC 3:7</a></p>\n<h2>Head-coverings in worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:4\">1CO 11:4</a></strong> <em>A man's uncovered head in worship signifies submission to his spiritual head, i.e., Jesus Christ</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:5-1Cor11:6\">1CO 11:5–11:6</a></strong> <em>A woman's covered head signifies proper submission to her husband.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:7\">1CO 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:13\">1CO 11:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's sight of humanity is not veiled</h2>\n<h3>The wicked foolishly boast that God does not see them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:12-Job22:14\">JOB 22:12–22:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:11\">PSA 10:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:7\">PSA 94:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:15\">ISA 29:15</a></p>\n<h3>God's people complain that God does not see their suffering</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:24\">PSA 44:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job13:24\">JOB 13:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:17\">PSA 69:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:14\">PSA 88:14</a></p>\n<h3>God sees all humanity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:24\">JOB 28:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:13\">GEN 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:21\">JOB 34:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:13\">PSA 33:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:3\">PSA 139:1–139:3</a></p>\n<h3>People's deeds will be made known</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:11\">JOB 28:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:21\">ISA 26:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:26\">MAT 10:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:2\">LUK 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:13\">1CO 3:13</a></p>\n<h2>The truth about God is sometimes veiled</h2>\n<h3>The veil worn by Moses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:13\">2CO 3:13</a></strong> <em>After speaking with God, Moses' face was radiant; the veil, possibly a loose part of his clothing pulled over his face, prevented the Israelites from seeing that the radiance did not last.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29-Exod34:35\">EXO 34:29–34:35</a></p>\n<h3>Lack of understanding of God's truth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:14-2Cor3:15\">2CO 3:14–3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:18\">ISA 44:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:65\">LAM 3:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14\">1CO 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:3\">2CO 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18\">EPH 4:18</a></p>\n<h2>The unveiling of God's truth</h2>\n<h3>God's hidden truth is revealed to believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:7-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:7–2:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:26\">COL 1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:4\">ISA 64:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:26\">ROM 16:25–16:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:16-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:16–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9\">EPH 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:3-Eph3:6\">EPH 3:3–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:10\">2TI 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:2-Titus1:3\">TIT 1:2–1:3</a></p>\n<h3>God's self-revelation at the end of the age</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:2-Dan12:4\">DAN 12:2–12:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:7-Isa25:8\">ISA 25:7–25:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19\">ROM 8:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></p>",
